2.7. Reversing payments you have not approved
:SKRSLUT.
.br
If you believe that your card has been used to make one or more
payments that you have not authorised, participated in or made, you
must contact &BANKNAVN. without delay after you have discovered the
unauthorised transaction. When assessing whether you have contacted
&BANKNAVN. in time, emphasis will be placed on your duty to review
your account movements on a regular basis, see Article 2.5. In any
event, you must contact &BANKNAVN. no later than 13 months after the
sum was withdrawn from your account.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
&BANKNAVN. will then investigate your complaint. While your complaint
is being investigated, the sum in dispute will normally be credited
to your account. If your complaint subsequently proves to be
unjustified, &BANKNAVN. will withdraw the sum from your account once
more. Should the investigation reveal that unauthorised use of your
card has occurred, &BANKNAVN. may hold you liable, see Article 2.9.
